Question based on Notes topic
--------------------------------

1) Explain in your own words the difference between using ; and && when chaining commands in the shell. 
   Provide a simple example for each case.

2) What would be the output (or behavior) of the following command sequence if ls file.txt fails (because file.txt does not exist)?
	ls file.txt && echo "File exists" ; echo "Command completed"

3) What is a command alias in Linux, and why might you want to use one? Please provide an explanation along with an example 
   of how to create a simple alias in a shell.

4) How can you make an alias permanent so that it persists across terminal sessions?

5) How would you view all currently defined aliases in your shell?

6) How can you remove an alias once it's been set? Provide the command to do so.

